verbose_text: The patient was treated with oral anti-hyperthyroidism drugs such as methimazole and propylthiouracil for 3 years, but repeated thyroid function tests during follow-up continued to show elevated levels of free thyroxine and free triiodothyronine acid along with a normal serum thyroid stimulating hormone level.
evidence: levels of free thyroxine and free triiodothyronine acid
